This method may be extended onto glucose measurement. An enzymatic incubation with glucose oxidase (GOx) was added for the catalytic generation of hydrogen peroxide from glucose samples. Under the optimum condition, a relationship between the recovery extent and the glucose concentrations was developed. Fig. 4
                         shows that the F/F0 values related to the amount of glucose in the range of 0.8–50 μM (with R2 = 0.9953). A limit of detection was estimated to be 0.11 μM for the glucose detection (3σ). This result was lower than or comparable to some other fluorescence methods (Table 1
                        ) [32–44]. Another series of replicated glucose measurements (0.8 μM) presented an RSD of 1.37%, which also showed a high reproducibility of this method.
